The paper deals with signal processing and communication applications, specifically in optical wireless communication systems. It discusses the optimization of the signal-to-noise-plus-distortion ratio (SNDR) to mitigate nonlinear distortions in these systems. This topic falls under the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT), communication and networking (cs.COMM), signal processing (cs.SI), networked systems (cs.NI), and machine learning (cs.LG).
